{"abstract":"In this paper, we consider Lie algebroids over commutative ringed spaces. Lie algebroids over ringed spaces unify the existing notion of Lie algebroids over smooth manifolds, complex manifolds, analytic spaces, algebraic varieties, and schemes. We show that the universal enveloping algebroid of a Lie algebroid possesses a natural filtration that yields a structure of a sheaf of quantum Poisson algebras. We establish a bijective correspondence between sheaves of quantum Poisson algebras and Lie algebroids. We show that this correspondence leads to an adjunction between the two categories. We discuss this bijective correspondence in particular cases of Lie algebroids over ringed spaces and highlight the subsequent results. To characterize non-flat Lie algebroid connections, we construct a sheaf of twisted universal enveloping algebras for a Lie algebroid using Lie algebroid (hyper)cohomology. We show that our construction yields some of the existing constructions for Lie-Rinehart algebras and holomorphic Lie algebroids. As another application, we study the deformation groupoid of a Lie algebroid using the second hypercohomology of the Lie algebroid.","authors":["SATYENDRAKUMAR MISHRA","ABHISHEK SARKAR"],"detailed_summary":"This research paper presents a unified framework for studying Lie algebroids by defining them over general commutative ringed spaces. This sheaf-theoretic approach encompasses and generalizes existing notions of Lie algebroids on smooth manifolds, complex manifolds, analytic spaces, and algebraic schemes, providing a common language for these diverse geometric contexts.\n\nThe primary objectives of the paper are twofold. First, it aims to establish a fundamental connection between Lie algebroids and quantum Poisson algebras at the level of sheaves, which the authors term 'algebroids'. Second, it seeks to characterize non-flat connections on Lie algebroids by constructing and analyzing twisted versions of their universal enveloping algebroids.\n\nTo achieve the first objective, the authors demonstrate that the universal enveloping algebroid U(O,L) of any Lie algebroid (O,L) is naturally endowed with a filtration that makes it a 'quantum Poisson algebroid'. They then establish a constructive, bijective correspondence that associates a unique Lie algebroid to any given quantum Poisson algebroid. This correspondence is elevated to a categorical level, proving that it forms an adjunction between the category of Lie algebroids and the category of quantum Poisson algebroids. For the second objective, the methodology involves Lie algebroid hypercohomology. The authors construct a 'twisted universal enveloping algebroid' U(O,L,ω) associated with a 2-cocycle ω. This construction is shown to be a sheaf of almost commutative filtered algebras.\n\nThe key results are significant. The paper successfully establishes the adjunction between Lie algebroids and quantum Poisson algebroids, providing a new structural perspective. The construction of U(O,L,ω) is shown to unify and generalize previous work on twisted universal enveloping algebras for Lie-Rinehart algebras and holomorphic Lie algebroids. A central finding is that for a locally free Lie algebroid L, a module structure over U(O,L,ω) is precisely equivalent to an L-connection with a specified curvature ω. Furthermore, the paper relates the second hypercohomology group H²(L,O) to the deformation theory of these algebraic structures, linking it to the deformation groupoid of the Lie algebroid.\n\nThe significance of this work lies in its powerful unification of concepts across differential and algebraic geometry. By providing a common framework, it facilitates the transfer of techniques and insights between these fields. The results have direct implications for representation theory, the study of D-modules on singular spaces, and the construction of moduli spaces of connections. The main contributions are the formalization of the Lie algebroid-quantum Poisson algebroid correspondence, the novel and unifying construction of twisted universal enveloping algebroids via hypercohomology, and the characterization of non-flat connections within this new algebraic framework.","gemini_analysis":{"future_directions":[],"key_findings":["The universal enveloping algebroid U(O,L) of a Lie algebroid (O,L) over a ringed space naturally possesses the structure of a quantum Poisson algebroid.","A bijective correspondence exists between sheaves of quantum Poisson algebras and Lie algebroids, which establishes an adjunction between their respective categories.","A twisted universal enveloping algebroid U(O,L,ω) can be constructed from a 2-cocycle ω, providing a unified framework that generalizes existing constructions for Lie-Rinehart algebras and holomorphic Lie algebroids.","For a locally free Lie algebroid (O,L), a U(O,L,ω)-module structure on an O-module E is equivalent to an L-connection on E with curvature of type ω.","The second hypercohomology group H²(L,O) of a Lie algebroid is linked to the deformation of sheaves of almost commutative filtered algebras and governs the deformation groupoid of the Lie algebroid.","The sheaf-theoretic definition of Lie algebroids over ringed spaces successfully unifies the concepts across smooth manifolds, complex manifolds, analytic spaces, and algebraic schemes."],"limitations":["The research is highly theoretical, focusing on unifying mathematical structures rather than solving a specific applied problem.","The framework is developed for commutative ringed spaces over a field of characteristic zero, potentially limiting its applicability in positive characteristic settings.","Key results, such as the characterization of connections and the Poincaré-Birkhoff-Witt theorem, are established for locally free Lie algebroids, and their extension to more general (e.g., quasi-coherent) Lie algebroids is not fully detailed.","As the provided text is an excerpt, a complete assessment of the work's limitations is not possible."],"methodology":"The research employs a theoretical and abstract algebraic approach, utilizing sheaf theory over commutative ringed spaces to unify the study of Lie algebroids. Key methods include: (1) Construction of the universal enveloping algebroid U(O,L) and analyzing its filtered structure to define a quantum Poisson algebroid. (2) Using categorical methods to establish an adjunction between the category of Lie algebroids and the category of quantum Poisson algebroids. (3) Applying Lie algebroid hypercohomology (specifically, 2-cocycles) to construct a sheaf of twisted universal enveloping algebras U(O,L,ω) to study non-flat connections.","research_area":"Algebraic and Differential Geometry, focusing on the theory of Lie algebroids, quantum Poisson algebras, and their connections to representation theory and mathematical physics.","research_impact":"This work provides a significant unification of Lie algebroid theory across diverse geometric settings (smooth, complex, algebraic), which can simplify proofs and reveal deeper structural connections. The established relationship between twisted universal enveloping algebroids and non-flat connections has direct implications for representation theory, the study of D-modules, and the construction of moduli spaces for connections. The research is poised to influence future work in noncommutative geometry, Poisson geometry, and deformation quantization, particularly on singular spaces."},"isPublic":true,"journalName":"arXiv","keywords":["Lie algebroids","ringed spaces","Lie-Rinehart algebras","universal enveloping algebra","quantum Poisson algebras","Lie algebroid hypercohomology","twisted universal enveloping algebroids","deformation groupoid"],"level":"info","message":"Metadata parsed successfully:","paperLink":"","publication_date":"2022-08-07T00:00:00.000Z","service":"research-companion-api","timestamp":"2025-08-08 17:34:24","title":"LIE ALGEBROIDS, QUANTUM POISSON ALGEBROIDS, AND LIE ALGEBROID CONNECTIONS"}
